    "7078de8b-b638-4054-aea9-51d0ddc2133d": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "00953de8-d4ad-454c-8943-f744b416e178": {
          "type": "title",
          "settings": {
            "title": "5. How to Wash",
            "title_size": "heading-size--small",
            "seo_h_tag": "h2"
          }
        },
        "a456cd81-6ca6-4b36-b9b4-9e630e5edb7c": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>It is optimal to wash inside out with cold water. Being that you are using an iron instead of a heatpress (which applies heat with more pressure, more evenly), we would recommend hang drying instead of in the dryer. If you decide to use a dryer, we'd recommend on low heat, inside out.</p><p>Everyone's irons, heat, pressure is different when using an iron, so test to find out what works best for you. Remember that you cannot overpress your transfers. The better they are pressed, the more durability they have through washing and drying. This is a good rule of thumb for most custom apparel, including <a href=\"https://ninjapatches.com/products/iron-on-patches-for-clothes\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Iron On Patches\">iron on patches</a>, to ensure the design stays permanent.</p>",
            "text_size": "regular"
          }
        },
